rk for the past 3 years. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   After 2+ years of playing EQ (which most people with 2 50+ chars on their accounts have done unless you're um *cough* ebay *cough) wouldn't you expect to be at least a tad bored with it?  I reckon Chanto played to have fun, not to achieve lvl 60, defeat all the boss mobs and have his name carved in the uber d00d's hall of fame like a 12 year old defeating the Legend of Zelda.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I'll even echo Quas' comments on Chanto.  (I never had a chance to group with him as Montyy, but I have no doubts he's equally skilled as a warrior like he was with his chanter.)  He's arguably one of the best chanters I've ever grouped with.  He never panicked in a bad pull, he never ditched the group due to his fragility of being a chanter, and he always just took it like a gnome and die should the occasion called for it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (Yeah just admit it, we've all grouped with chanters who either run around in circles waiting for someone to root a mob off him, gate, or run to the zone.  Even at high lvls.)  Most importantly, he played to have fun, and with a sense of humor unlike a lot of people I've grouped with who seemed to have a stick up their ass.<br><br>He'll be missed, but I'm glad I'll have a chance to adventure with him again in another game. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><CENTER><TABLE><TR><TD><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://arnemetia.homestead.com/files/EQimages/RehmyPPGSig.gif" BORDER=0 ALT="Click to see character sta